sometimes loaded expression were part of larger rhetorical structures that gainsay the uses to which the key terms have been put in modern historiography.It has been more than fifty years since a book has been devoted to analyzing the careers of these three critics, and never before has their role in the historiography and periodization of American art been analyzed. The conclusions drawn from this close rereading of well-known texts challenge the fundamental nature of “historical context” in American art history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aArt criticismzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aArt, AmericanxHistoriography. 7aART / American / General.2bisacsh  a.  aArt-Idea.  aClarence Cook Art History Art.  aCriticism Nineteenth-Century American Art.  aJames Jackson Jarves.  aKaren L. Georgi.  aWilliam J. Stillman.  aunited states.  aus.  ausa.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311074526940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271062471?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271062471423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271062471/original  a978-3-11-074526-9  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK